  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A sanction is a consequence imposed for violating a rule. In legal systems, sanctions take specific institutional forms: fines, imprisonment, probation, asset forfeiture, injunctions, damages. The sanction is what distinguishes a legal rule from a suggestion — it is the coercive backing that makes law enforceable.",
